actions.text: The House Committee on Rules reported an original measure, H. Rept. 102-1021, by Ms. Slaughter.

Rule provides for consideration of the conference report to H.R. 5334. Upon the adoption of this resolution it shall be in order to consider the conference report to accompany H.R. 5334. All points of order against the conference report and against its consideration are waived. The conference report shall be considered as read.
Placed on the House Calendar, Calendar No. 236.
DEBATE - The House proceeded with one hour of debate.
The previous question was ordered without objection.
On agreeing to the resolution Agreed to by the Yeas and Nays: 303 - 101 (Roll no. 475).
Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

official_title: Waiving points of order against the conference report to accompany the bill (H.R. 5334) to amend and extend certain laws relating to housing and community development, and for other purposes, and against the consideration of such conference report.

summary.text: Sets forth the rule for the consideration of H.R. 5334 (housing and community development).
